msgid "Viewport and canvas transforms"
msgstr "Athraíonn amharc agus canbhás"

msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Réamhrá"

msgid ""
"The goal of this tutorial is to teach a way for feeding input events to the "
"Input with a position in the correct coordinate system."
msgstr ""
"Is é aidhm an rang teagaisc seo bealach a mhúineadh chun imeachtaí ionchuir "
"a bheathú don Ionchur le suíomh sa chóras comhordaithe ceart."

msgid ""
"A more extensive description of all coordinate systems and 2d transforms is "
"available in :ref:`doc_2d_coordinate_systems`."
msgstr ""
"Tá cur síos níos fairsinge ar gach córas comhordaithe agus ar na "
"claochruithe 2d ar fáil in:ref: `doc_2d_coordinate_systems`."

msgid "Canvas transform"
msgstr "Athrú canbhás"

msgid ""
"As mentioned in the previous tutorial, :ref:`doc_canvas_layers`, every "
"CanvasItem node (remember that Node2D and Control based nodes use CanvasItem "
"as their common root) will reside in a *Canvas Layer*. Every canvas layer "
"has a transform (translation, rotation, scale, etc.) that can be accessed as "
"a :ref:`Transform2D <class_Transform2D>`."
msgstr ""
"Mar a luadh sa rang teagaisc roimhe seo, :ref:`doc_canvas_layers`, beidh "
"gach nód CanvasItem (cuimhnigh go n-úsáideann Node2D agus nóid atá bunaithe "
"ar Rialú CanvasItem mar a bhfréamh coitianta) i *Ciseal Canbhás*. Tá "
"claochlú (aistriúchán, rothlú, scála, etc.) ag gach ciseal canbháis ar "
"féidir rochtain a fháil air mar :ref:`Transform2D <class_Transform2D>`."

msgid ""
"Also covered in the previous tutorial, nodes are drawn by default in Layer "
"0, in the built-in canvas. To put nodes in a different layer, "
"a :ref:`CanvasLayer <class_CanvasLayer>` node can be used."
msgstr ""
"Clúdaithe freisin sa rang teagaisc roimhe seo, tarraingítear nóid de réir "
"réamhshocraithe i Sraith 0, sa chanbhás ionsuite. Chun nóid a chur i sraith "
"eile, is féidir nód :ref:`CanvasLayer <class_CanvasLayer>` a úsáid."

msgid "Global canvas transform"
msgstr "Athrú canbhás domhanda"

msgid ""
"Viewports also have a Global Canvas transform (also a :ref:`Transform2D "
"<class_Transform2D>`). This is the master transform and affects all "
"individual *Canvas Layer* transforms. Generally, this is primarily used in "
"Godot's CanvasItem Editor."
msgstr ""
"Tá trasfhoirmiú Canbhás Domhanda ag Viewports freisin (:tag:`Transform2D "
"<class_Transform2D>` freisin). Is é seo an máistir claochlú agus a théann i "
"bhfeidhm ar gach duine aonair * Ciseal Chanbhás *. Go ginearálta, úsáidtear "
"é seo go príomha in Eagarthóir CanvasItem Godot."

msgid "Stretch transform"
msgstr "Athrú síneadh"

msgid ""
"Finally, viewports have a *Stretch Transform*, which is used when resizing "
"or stretching the screen. This transform is used internally (as described "
"in :ref:`doc_multiple_resolutions`), but can also be manually set on each "
"viewport."
msgstr ""
"Faoi dheireadh, tá *Stretch Transform* ag viewports, a úsáidtear agus an "
"scáileán á athrú nó ag síneadh. Úsáidtear an claochlú seo go hinmheánach "
"(mar a thuairiscítear in:ref: `doc_multiple_resolutions`), ach is féidir é a "
"shocrú de láimh ar gach amharc freisin."

msgid "Window transform"
msgstr "Athrú fuinneoige"

msgid ""
"The root viewport is a :ref:`Window <class_Window>`. In order to scale and "
"position the *Window's* content as described "
"in :ref:`doc_multiple_resolutions`, each :ref:`Window <class_Window>` "
"contains a *window transform*. It is for example responsible for the black "
"bars at the *Window's* sides so that the *Viewport* is displayed with a "
"fixed aspect ratio."
msgstr ""
"Is é an t-amharc fréimhe ná :ref:`Fuinneog <class_Window>`. Chun inneachar "
"an *Fuinneog* a scála agus a shuíomh mar a thuairiscítear "
"i :ref:`doc_multiple_resolutions`, tá *claochlú fhuinneog* i "
"ngach :ref:`Fuinneog <class_Window>`. Tá sé freagrach mar shampla as na "
"barraí dubha ar thaobhanna na *Fuinneog* ionas go dtaispeánfar an "
"*Amharcport* le cóimheas seasta treoíochta."

